RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 1 5F Dirt CR: 62. Maiden Special Weight Purse 20000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUMP THE QUEUE quickly moved to the front, set the pace on the inside, turned back a challenge from DARE MIGHTY THINGS, and won going away. DARE MIGHTY THINGS sat just off the pace, moved up alongside JUMP THE QUEUE near the quarter pole and lacked the rally needed. EL PASO stalked three wide into the opening turn, and lacked a closing response. HE LIKES WINNING trailed throughout.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 62. Maiden Claiming Purse 11500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STARLIGHT LANE bumped leaving the gate, steadied in close quarters leaving the backstretch, found running room along the rail into the stretch and won driving. GOLDIE SOCKS vied between foes early, moved up alongside HERE'S LEXIE to challenge the lead, and inched clear for second honors. HERE'S LEXIE contended the early pace from the three path, held a slim advantage into the lane, and was worn down through the stretch settling for third. SHES A COOL CAT bumped away from the gate, raced at the back of the pack, the rider took a hold nearing traffic when entering the far turn, swung out into the lane, and produced a mild bid. SMOKIN JOY chased outside and gave way.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 3 5F Dirt CR: 61. Maiden Special Weight Purse 20000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ASAMATTEROFFACTIDO hurried inside to clear the lead, turned back a challenge from SIZZLIN ROSE, and drew away under a brisk hand ride. BROKEN PROMISES lagged early, shifted out to the four path into the stretch, and closed gamely to score second. SIZZLIN ROSE hurried away, loomed boldly near the quarter pole, was no match for the winner in the stretch and was nipped at the wire. KULSUM vied hard outside, fanned four wide through the opening turn, and rallied mildly through stretch. LIGHTERANQUICKER offered a mild bid from the rail and was unable to improve position. BURNING UP showed early speed, fanned three wide, and tired.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BEAUTIFUL CALL gave chase under encouragement through the backstretch, gained closer order into the final turn from a rail position, shifted out into the two path, closed gradually on the leader, dug in, in the final yards and was up just in time. DARLA'S FURY sped to the front under a snug hold, moved clear when released, was showing signs of tiring at the head of the lane, and was rundown. PUNCH PERFECT trailed the field early, advanced quickly through the final turn, and failed to threaten in the drive. VIOLET CITY tracked the pacesetter from the rail, and came up empty in the drive. RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 79. Allowance Purse 23000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IT'S A FACT sat in striking position while four wide, moved up along ARGENTINA CRIES at the five-sixteenth pole to challenge the front, dueled determinedly through the stretch, continued to match strides under heavy urging, and wore down rival while inching clear to score the win. ARGENTINA CRIES (IRE) brushed early while vying for the lead, contested the pace outside of LIL ZAPPER then was joined in the final turn by IT'S A FACT, responded gamely to the confrontation, match the rivals' energy under steady coaxing then gave way grudgingly deep stretch. BIG BAD INTAGLIO bumped away from the gate, settled at the back of the pack from the three path, gained ground on the dueling foes in the stretch and missed. VANTASTICCANAVERAL tracked wide through the backstretch, and offered a late mild rally. MUDINATOR steadied in traffic early, and faded gradually in the drive. PADDYS ROCKET sat in range, fanned 3w in the far turn, and gave way. LIL ZAPPER contested the early pace from the rail, was unable to move on with rival and faded.

ENTRY.OWNER: C and H Duggan Farms Ltd
